correct-top.narrative:
Right! The first line of your code in the stack trace is usually where the problem is. You open ProductList.jsx and see line 12:

const items = products.map(p => <li>{p.name}</li>);

The error says 'null' has no '.map'. What does this tell you?

end-good.narrative:
You add a guard check:

if (!products) return <p>Loading...</p>;

Now the component shows a loading message while products is null (like during the initial API fetch), and renders the list once data arrives. The crash is gone.
